eb | accessdate = 13 March 2017 | url = http://www.okayplayer.com/interviews/rjd2-gives-you-his-third-hand-200703065619.html | url-status = live | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111027223703/http://www.okayplayer.com/interviews/rjd2-gives-you-his-third-hand-200703065619.html | archivedate = 27 October 2011 | title = RJD2 Gives You His Third Hand | date = 6 March 2007 | website = [[Okayplayer]] | first = Sean | last = Kantrowitz }}</ref> hip hop and soul composer [[Adrian Younge]],<ref>{{cite web | accessdate = 12 March 2017 | url = https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/adrian-younge-interview | title = Adrian Younge Is Timeless | date = 15 October 2013 | publisher = [[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] | website = noisey.vice.com | quote = ''Q'': Do you think you'll ever leave that soul music chamber?{{break}}''Adrian Younge'': Never! Oddly enough, I plan to commence work on more psychedelic rock records; however, the psychedelic rock I'm inspired by has a lot of soul like King Crimson, [[Iron Butterfly]], [[Bo Hansson]], etc. }}</ref> film director [[Hal Hartley]],<ref>{{cite web | accessdate = 12 March 2017 | url = http://filmmakermagazine.com/archives/issues/fall1992/simple_laws.php#.WMXWC39tjKE | title = The simple laws of filmmaking | first = James | last = Schamus | authorlink = James Schamus | magazine = [[Filmmaker (magazine)|Filmmaker]] | quote = ''Hal Hartley'': I made a list of all the influences I could remember from the time I was 18 to the present. Here it goes: Robert Fripp and King Crimson [...] | date = Fall 1992 }}</ref> and folk-pop singer [[Ian Kelly (songwriter)|Ian Kelly]].<ref>{{cite web | accessdate = 13 March 2017 | url = http://canadianbeats.ca/2015/07/15/interview-ian-kelly/ | title = Interview \u2013 Ian Kelly | date = 15 July 2015 | first = Remington | last = Fioraso | website = canadianbeats.ca }}</ref>\n\nIn addition to their influence regarding the music industry, the band has also influenced various parts of popular culture. One example can be identified through the name of the supernatural \u201cStand\u201d ability of the character, [[Diavolo (JoJo's Bizarre Adventure)|Diavolo]], in the Japanese anime and manga, [[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure]]; which was created by [[Hirohiko Araki]].\n\n== Members ==\n{{Main|List of King Crimson members}}\n'''Current members'''\n*[[Robert Fripp]] \u2013 guitar, keyboards, mellotron, electronics {{small|(1969\u20131974, 1981\u20131984, 1994\u20132004, 2007\u20132008, 2013\u2013present)}}\n*[[Mel Collins]] \u2013 saxophones, flute, bass flute, mellotron, backing vocals {{small|(1970\u20131972, 2013\u2013present)}}\n*[[Tony Levin]] \u2013 bass, Chapman stick, synthesisers, backing vocals {{small|(1981\u20131984, 1994\u20131998, 2003\u20132004, 2007\u20132008, 2013\u2013present)}}\n*[[Pat Mastelotto]] \u2013 drums, percussion, programming {{small|(1994\u20132004, 2007\u20132008, 2013\u2013present)}}\n*[[Gavin Harrison]] \u2013 drums, percussion {{small|(2007\u20132008, 2013\u2013present)}}\n*[[Jakko Jakszyk]] \u2013 lead vocals, guitar, flute, keyboards {{small|(2013\u2013present)}}\n*[[Jeremy Stacey]] \u2013 drums, keyboards {{small|(2016\u2013present)}}\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|King Crimson discography}}\n\n'''Studio albums'''\n* ''[[In the Court of the Crimson King]]'' (1969)\n* ''[[In the Wake of Poseidon]]'' (1970)\n* ''[[Lizard (album)|Lizard]]'' (1970)\n* ''[[Islands (King Crimson album)|Islands]]'' (1971)\n* ''[[Larks' Tongues in Aspic]]'' (1973)\n* ''[[Starless and Bible Black]]'' (1974)\n* ''[[Red (King Crimson album)|Red]]'' (1974)\n* ''[[Discipline (King Crimson album)|Discipline]]'' (1981)\n* ''[[Beat (King Crimson album)|Beat]]'' (1982)\n* ''[[Three of a Perfect Pair]]'' (1984)\n* ''[[Thrak|THRAK]]'' (1995)\n* ''[[The Construkction of Light]]'' (2000)\n* ''[[The Power to Believe]]'' (2003)\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n* <cite id=refBuckley2003>{{Cite book |last=Buckley |first=Peter |title=The Rough Guide to Rock |publisher=Rough Guides |year=2003 |location=London |isbn=1-85828-201-2 |url=https://archive.org/details/rockroughguide00buck }}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [http://www.dgmlive.com/ Discipline Global Mobile Live]\n* [http://www.crimsonjazztrio.com/ Crimson Jazz Trio]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060804182039/http://elephant-talk.com/ Elephant Talk]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20101229225627/http://projekction.net/ ProjeKction]\n* {{discogs artist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{King Crimson}}\n{{Adrian Belew}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n\n[[Category:King Crimson| ]]\n[[Category:English art rock groups]]\n[[Category:English progressive rock groups]]\n[[Category:Free improvisation ensembles]]\n[[Category:Island Records artists]]\n[[Category:Caroline Records artists]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Polydor Records artists]]\n[[Category:Virgin Records artists]]\n[[Category:E.G. Records artists]]\n[[Category:Vertigo Records artists]]\n[[Category:Warner Records artists]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1968]]\n[[Category:Musical groups disestablished in 1974]]\n[[Category:Musical groups reestablished in 1981]]\n[[Category:Musical groups disestablished in 1984]]\n[[Category:Musical groups reestablished in 1994]]\n[[Category:Musical groups disestablished in 2004]]\n[[Category:Musical groups reestablished in 2007]]\n[[Category:Musical groups disestablished in 2008]]\n[[Category:Musical groups reestablished in 2013]]\n[[Category:Musical quartets]]\n[[Category:Musical quintets]]\n[[Category:Discipline Global Mobile artists]]\n[[Category:Articles which contain graphical timelines]]\n[[Category:Post-progressive musicians]]\n[[Category:Proto-prog musicians]]\n[[Category:Symphonic rock groups]]\n", "name_user": "95.150.171.86", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_Crimson"}
{"title_page": "Cat Rapes Dog", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{notability|Music|date=April 2014}}\n{{refimprove|date=April 2014}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Cat Rapes Dog\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| landscape       = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = Sweden\n| genre           = [[Electropunk]], [[electronic body music|EBM]], [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]]\n| years_active    = {{start date|1984}}\u2013 2009, 2019-\n| label           = \n| associated_acts = [[And One]], [[Atari Cowboy]]\n| current_members = Magnus Fransson<br />Annelie Bertilsson<br />Jonas Awertoft<br />John Wreibo Lindqwister\n| past_members    = Joel Rydstr\u00f6m<br />Laszlo Hago\n}}\n'''Cat Rapes Dog''' is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[electropunk]], [[electronic body music|EBM]] and [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] band, formed in 1984 by [[Joel Rydstr\u00f6m]] and [[Magnus Fransson]]. \n\nInitially the band self-released a number of albums on cassette, (then a trend followed by many independent acts of their type), plus a cassette album & vinyl singles on Swedish label [[Front Music Production]].\n\nBetween 1989 and 1991 Cat Rapes Dog released three studio albums on [[KK Records]], a Belgian independent label specialising in [[new beat]], [[Electronic body music|EBM]] and [[Industrial music|industrial]] acts (such as [[Front Line Assembly]] or [[Vomito Negro (band)|Vomito Negro]]) that released over 300 titles between 1987 and 1996. Multiple Cat Rapes Dog albums were later released on Swedish independent labels [[Energy Rekords]] ([[Die Krupps]], [[VNV Nation]], [[Front 242]], etc.) and [[Subspace Communications]] ([[Covenant (band)|Covenant]], [[Apoptygma Berzerk]], etc.) and on [[Artoffact Records]] of [[Toronto, Canada]] in 2013. Additional retrospective compilations have also been released by the above mentioned labels.\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Albums ===\n* Cat Rapes Dog (1986, [[Compact audio cassette|MC]])\n* Nekronomikon (1987, [[Compact audio cassette|MC]])\n* Property Produces Bodily Injury (1987, [[Compact audio cassette|MC]])\n* Maximum Overdrive (1989)\n* God, Guns & Gasoline (1990)\n* Superluminal (1991)\n* Schizophrenia (1993)\n* Moosehair Underwear (1993)\n* Biodegradable (1995)\n* Fuck Nature (1995)\n* More Than You Bargained For (1995)\n* The Secrets of God (1998)\n* People As Prey (1999)\n* Life Was Sweet (2013)\n\n=== Singles and EPs ===\n* Columna Vertebralis (1989)\n* Down & Out (1998)\n* American Dream 7\" (1990)\n* Chuckahomo Bridge 12\" (1990)\n* Fundamental 12\" (1990)\n* Madman / True Love 7\" (1990)\n* I Sometimes Wish I Was Famous (1991) (A Swedish [[Depeche Mode]] cover album: CRD collaborates with one track: \"Something to Do\" in which they altered some of the lyrics.)\n* The Banzai Beats (1991)\n* Superluminal (1991)\n* Trojan Whores (1992)\n* Moosewear (1993)\n* Nej till EU (1994)\n* Sucking Dry (1994)\n* Mot\u00f6rhead Tribute (1995) (A Scandinavian [[Mot\u00f6rhead]] cover album: CRD collaborates with \"[[Deaf Forever]]\".)\n* Motorman (1998)\n* Workers of The World (1998)\n* Miaow at the Moon (2003)\n\n== Remixes for other artists done by Cat Rapes Dog ==\n# [[Das Ich]] - \"Gottes Tod\" (1999)\n# [[Sara Noxx]] - \"Earth Song\" (feat. [[Project Pitchfork]]) (2008)\n# [[Atari Cowboy]] - \"Autotune Your Life\" (2012)\n# [[Atari Cowboy]] - \"Never Follow Anything\" (2012)\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180817204912/http://www.crd.se/ Official homepage]\n* {{musicbrainz artist|id=9bece46d-c7d2-400f-ac1e-bbdc14861619}}\n* [http://www.discogs.com/artist/8947-Cat-Rapes-Dog Discogs Entry]\n* [http://cybernoise.com/info/artist.php?1173 artist information/discography page at CyberNoise]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Electronic body music groups]]\n[[Category:Swedish industrial music groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1984]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{notability|Music|date=April 2014}}\n{{refimprove|date=April 2014}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Cat Rapes Dog\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| landscape       = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = Sweden\n| genre           = [[Electropunk]], [[electronic body music|EBM]], [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]]\n| years_active    = {{start date|1984}}\u2013 2009, 2019-\n| label           = \n| associated_acts = [[And One]], [[Atari Cowboy]]\n| website         = {{URL|http://www.crd.se}}\n| current_members = Magnus Fransson<br />Annelie Bertilsson<br />Jonas Awertoft<br />John Wreibo Lindqwister\n| past_members    = Joel Rydstr\u00f6m<br />Laszlo Hago\n}}\n'''Cat Rapes Dog''' is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[electropunk]], [[electronic body music|EBM]] and [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] band, formed in 1984 by [[Joel Rydstr\u00f6m]] and [[Magnus Fransson]]. \n\nInitially the band self-released a number of albums on cassette, (then a trend followed by many independent acts of their type), plus a cassette album & vinyl singles on Swedish label [[Front Music Production]].\n\nBetween 1989 and 1991 Cat Rapes Dog released three studio albums on [[KK Records]], a Belgian independent label specialising in [[new beat]], [[Electronic body music|EBM]] and [[Industrial music|industrial]] acts (such as [[Front Line Assembly]] or [[Vomito Negro (band)|Vomito Negro]]) that released over 300 titles between 1987 and 1996. Multiple Cat Rapes Dog albums were later released on Swedish independent labels [[Energy Rekords]] ([[Die Krupps]], [[VNV Nation]], [[Front 242]], etc.) and [[Subspace Communications]] ([[Covenant (band)|Covenant]], [[Apoptygma Berzerk]], etc.) and on [[Artoffact Records]] of [[Toronto, Canada]] in 2013. Additional retrospective compilations have also been released by the above mentioned labels.\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Albums ===\n* Cat Rapes Dog (1986, [[Compact audio cassette|MC]])\n* Nekronomikon (1987, [[Compact audio cassette|MC]])\n* Property Produces Bodily Injury (1987, [[Compact audio cassette|MC]])\n* Maximum Overdrive (1989)\n* God, Guns & Gasoline (1990)\n* Superluminal (1991)\n* Schizophrenia (1993)\n* Moosehair Underwear (1993)\n* Biodegradable (1995)\n* Fuck Nature (1995)\n* More Than You Bargained For (1995)\n* The Secrets of God (1998)\n* People As Prey (1999)\n* Life Was Sweet (2013)\n\n=== Singles and EPs ===\n* Columna Vertebralis (1989)\n* Down & Out (1998)\n* American Dream 7\" (1990)\n* Chuckahomo Bridge 12\" (1990)\n* Fundamental 12\" (1990)\n* Madman / True Love 7\" (1990)\n* I Sometimes Wish I Was Famous (1991) (A Swedish [[Depeche Mode]] cover album: CRD collaborates with one track: \"Something to Do\" in which they altered some of the lyrics.)\n* The Banzai Beats (1991)\n* Superluminal (1991)\n* Trojan Whores (1992)\n* Moosewear (1993)\n* Nej till EU (1994)\n* Sucking Dry (1994)\n* Mot\u00f6rhead Tribute (1995) (A Scandinavian [[Mot\u00f6rhead]] cover album: CRD collaborates with \"[[Deaf Forever]]\".)\n* Motorman (1998)\n* Workers of The World (1998)\n* Miaow at the Moon (2003)\n\n== Remixes for other artists done by Cat Rapes Dog ==\n# [[Das Ich]] - \"Gottes Tod\" (1999)\n# [[Sara Noxx]] - \"Earth Song\" (feat. [[Project Pitchfork]]) (2008)\n# [[Atari Cowboy]] - \"Autotune Your Life\" (2012)\n# [[Atari Cowboy]] - \"Never Follow Anything\" (2012)\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180817204912/http://www.crd.se/ Official homepage]\n* {{musicbrainz artist|id=9bece46d-c7d2-400f-ac1e-bbdc14861619}}\n* [http://www.discogs.com/artist/8947-Cat-Rapes-Dog Discogs Entry]\n* [http://cybernoise.com/info/artist.php?1173 artist information/discography page at CyberNoise]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Electronic body music groups]]\n[[Category:Swedis