who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. She has been a member of the [[Puerto Rico women's national football team|Puerto Rico women's national team]].\n\n==Early life==\nHilliard was raised in [[Medina, Ohio|Medina]], [[Ohio]].<ref name=FIUA/>\n\n==International career==\nHilliard qualified to play for Puerto Rico through her maternal grandparents.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/@kamikazepilot42/embracing-roots-has-hilliard-on-precipice-of-puerto-rico-national-team-southeast-missouri-state-8e60780fdb09|title=Embracing roots has Hilliard on precipice of Puerto Rico national team, Southeast Missouri State soccer history|first=Josh|last=Mlot|date=6 May 2017|accessdate=13 April 2020|website=Medium|quote=My mom didn\u2019t grow up there (in Puerto Rico), but my mom\u2019s parents grew up there, and so did my great grandparents}}</ref> She capped for ''Las Boricuas'' at senior level during the [[2018 CONCACAF Women's Championship qualification]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://femenino.elhuracanazulpr.com/2018/05/puerto-rico-cierra-con-victoria-ante.html|title=Puerto Rico cierra con victoria ante Aruba|first=Javier|last=Torres|language=es|date=12 May 2018|accessdate=13 April 2020|website=Seleccion Femenina de Futbol de Puerto Rico}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hilliard, Jasmin}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Women's association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Women's association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rico women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican people of African-American descent]]\n[[Category:American women's soccer players]]\n[[Category:Soccer players from Ohio]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Cuyahoga County, Ohio]]\n[[Category:People from Middleburg Heights, Ohio]]\n[[Category:People from Medina, Ohio]]\n[[Category:African-American women's soccer players]]\n[[Category:American sportspeople of Puerto Ri